persecution /ˌpɜːsɪˈkjuːʃən/

(persecutions) 

1. N-COUNT Persecution is cruel and unfair treatment of a person or group, especially because of their religious or political beliefs, or their race. (尤指因宗教、政治信仰或种族而遭受的) 迫害 

例： ...the persecution of minorities. …对少数派的迫害。 

例： ...victims of political persecution. …政治迫害的受害者。

